from hamachi gordon hamachi subject re honda accord brake problem joni ciarlettum write my honda accord just hit the magic mile mark and now all sort of thing be begin to go bad the latest problem i be experience be with my brake they still stop the car fine but once i be stop completely my brake pedal will sink another or inch all by itself if feel really strange and i be worry my brake will quit work one of these day i check my brake fluid and the reservoir wa full but the fluid itself look really dirty like dirty oil i call my mechanic and he tell me i need a new brake master cylinder which will cost me a whop you be not alone my honda accord with mile on it start show the same behavior i replace the brake master cylinder myself it take about an hmy and cost about sure beat pay to have someone else do it if i want to rebuild my own master cylinder instead of put in a rebuild one it would have cost only to for the rebuild kit the honda brake master cylinder be easy to get to two bolt attach it to the engine compartment two brake line enter the master cylinder the tricky part wa that the brake line be stick tight my craftsman open end wrench round off the bolt head i have to use vise grip to loosen those sucker wow best invention since slice bread after that it wa very easy bolt the new part in place add new brake fluid and bleed the brake thi be quite easy even for a beginner my local auto part store have a repair manual for the honda accord it have detail diagram of the master brake cylinder and a step-by-step procedure for replace it 